  "text": "Cocaine locomotor sensitization experiments were adapted from [CITATION_1] . On Day 3, mice were randomly assigned to the following treatment groups: saline/saline (SAL/SAL; n ¼ 9), LEV/saline (LEV/SAL; n ¼ 9), saline/ cocaine (SAL/COC; n ¼ 9), or LEV/cocaine (LEV/COC; n ¼ 9), and locomotion before and after injection with each drug was measured on Days 3-7 as described above. Ten days after the fifth cocaine injection, all mice were retested after injection of saline followed by saline on Day 18, saline followed by 15 mg/kg i.p. cocaine on Day 19, and LEV 100 mg/kg i.p. followed by cocaine 15 mg/kg i.p. on Day 20.",
